        <body>
            <div xml:id="KT379-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">notumalar varaivuḻit tōḻi aṟattoṭu niṉṟatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">The confidante standing firm in duty, when the
                    marriage with strangers [is imminent]. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT379">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> iṉṟiyāṇ ṭaiyaṉō tōḻi kuṉṟattup</l>
                    <l> paḻaṅkuḻi yakaḻnta kāṉavaṉ kiḻaṅkiṉoṭu</l>
                    <l> kaṇṇakaṉ ṟūmaṇi peṟūu nāṭa</l>
                    <l> ṉaṟivukāḻk koḷḷu maḷavaic ciṟutoṭi</l>
                    <l> yemmil varukuvai nīyeṉa</l>
                    <l> pomma lōti nīvi yōṉē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l> Where [is] he today, friend,</l>
                    <l> who stroked [my] thick hair,</l>
                    <l> saying “you will come to our house,</l>
                    <l rend="indent3"> [you with] small bracelets, when knowledge is ripe ”,</l>
                    <l> the man from a land,</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> where the forest man, who has dug a pit for fruit on the hill,</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> [and] obtains, together with the bulbous roots, a jewel</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> of eye-widening purity.</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
